1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 40-05-22 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to golf carts on city streets.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 40-05-22 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 40-05-22. Golf carts on city streets.
7 The governing body of a city may allow by an ordinance the operation of golf carts on the
8 city streets. The ordinance may not allow a golf cart on federal, state, or county highways in the
9 city, except for the perpendicular crossing of these highways. The ordinance may not allow the
10 operation of a golf cart on city streets except for daytime travel between the owner's place of
11 residence and a golf courseat night. Golf carts that are allowed to operate on the city streets as
12 the result of an ordinance are exempt from the title, registration, and equipment provisions of
13 title 39.
